1
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:30,770
=My Dear Guardian=

2
00:01:31,340 --> 00:01:34,120
=Episode 33=

3
00:01:35,559 --> 00:01:37,359
How long do we have to wait?

4
00:01:37,948 --> 00:01:40,549
Is it that hard to find
the building's information?

5
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:43,480
This structure was built by
the Chinese government.

6
00:01:43,521 --> 00:01:46,839
It's for helping people
who are poor and have no money,

7
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:50,419
and then after a few years,

8
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:53,319
all files and all investments,

9
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:55,689
international investments are pulled,

10
00:01:55,730 --> 00:01:58,440
and then this structure is frozen.

11
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,500
How about now?

12
00:02:03,353 --> 00:02:06,265
Now, we need to find people
who know about this situation...

13
00:02:06,306 --> 00:02:09,426
and try to help us make this great plan.

14
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:12,630
My father will be dead
before you finish planning!

15
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,320
Calm down! Calm down!

16
00:02:19,898 --> 00:02:20,778
Hello.

17
00:02:21,551 --> 00:02:22,471
What is it?

18
00:02:23,166 --> 00:02:24,320
Okay, okay.

19
00:02:24,871 --> 00:02:26,030
Now, we have good news.

20
00:02:27,006 --> 00:02:27,861
In 10 minutes,

21
00:02:27,902 --> 00:02:30,200
Officer Chen from the Chinese
government will be coming,

22
00:02:30,241 --> 00:02:32,491
and he has what we need.

23
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,519
Have a seat.

24
00:02:38,711 --> 00:02:40,711
It's hard to get these blueprints.

25
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,360
It's a young officer named Liang Mu Ze,

26
00:02:43,401 --> 00:02:46,511
who accidentally found
that the Corps of Engineers of his unit...

27
00:02:46,552 --> 00:02:48,602
was involved in
the construction of this structure...

28
00:02:48,643 --> 00:02:50,603
when they came to Isaia for a
peace operation a few years ago.

29
00:02:51,392 --> 00:02:53,981
He insisted on digging out the information
about the structure's construction...

30
00:02:54,022 --> 00:02:56,582
of the Corps of Engineer
from the mountain of papers.

31
00:02:56,888 --> 00:02:58,168
But the blueprints were incomplete.

32
00:02:59,359 --> 00:03:00,204
So...

33
00:03:00,245 --> 00:03:03,164
He spent time and found an
old soldier who's soon retired.

34
00:03:04,104 --> 00:03:06,440
The soldier experienced
the reconstruction back then.

35
00:03:07,516 --> 00:03:10,320
He helped Liang Mu Ze to
redraw the missing parts of the map.

36
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:20,320
He didn't tell you about this in
advance because he was afraid that...

37
00:03:20,361 --> 00:03:22,560
you'd be disappointed
if no result was found.

38
00:03:23,407 --> 00:03:26,040
He could've passed you
these blueprints by himself,

39
00:03:26,854 --> 00:03:28,951
but it'll gain more
attention from the police...

40
00:03:29,271 --> 00:03:31,000
of Isaia if it's submitted by me.

41
00:03:33,089 --> 00:03:33,968
Thanks.

42
00:03:34,326 --> 00:03:35,206
Thank you.

43
00:03:36,191 --> 00:03:38,591
The embassy has been closely
following the developments.

44
00:03:39,022 --> 00:03:41,750
We'll try our best to
push them to act fast...

45
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:44,271
and rescue your father
as well as solve the case.

46
00:03:44,782 --> 00:03:46,173
You need to learn patience too,

47
00:03:46,782 --> 00:03:47,760
do not panic.

48
00:03:49,685 --> 00:03:50,565
Okay.

49
00:04:09,031 --> 00:04:10,320
Where are you taking me?

50
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,070
Professor!

51
00:05:20,494 --> 00:05:22,294
Old master, we're in trouble.

52
00:05:32,108 --> 00:05:33,040
Xia Chu.

53
00:05:33,271 --> 00:05:34,271
Liang Mu Ze.

54
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:37,440
Are you all right? What's the matter?

55
00:05:39,032 --> 00:05:41,640
Mahadi told me that
my father has been rescued!

56
00:05:43,801 --> 00:05:44,681
Thank you.

57
00:05:45,991 --> 00:05:47,911
Thanks for everything
you've done for us.

58
00:05:49,459 --> 00:05:51,791
Then when are you going to come back?

59
00:05:53,897 --> 00:05:55,497
After taking care of Tang Lin's funeral.

60
00:05:56,563 --> 00:05:57,443
Who is Tang Lin?

61
00:05:58,182 --> 00:05:59,320
He is my father's assistant...

62
00:05:59,991 --> 00:06:01,760
and it was him who
lured my father to Isaia.

63
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:03,960
At last,

64
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,871
he took the bullet for my father.

65
00:06:07,512 --> 00:06:08,480
He's gone.

66
00:06:08,521 --> 00:06:09,467
Is uncle all right?

67
00:06:09,508 --> 00:06:10,503
He's fine.

68
00:06:10,544 --> 00:06:12,702
He's currently cooperating with
the local police investigations.

69
00:06:12,743 --> 00:06:14,063
I can see him tomorrow.

70
00:06:15,031 --> 00:06:15,911
Okay, then.

71
00:06:16,906 --> 00:06:18,240
Get some rest today.

72
00:06:19,203 --> 00:06:20,280
We'll talk about it when you get back.

73
00:06:25,034 --> 00:06:26,594
Goodnight, Braised Egg.

74
00:06:27,873 --> 00:06:28,800
I'm going to hang up.

75
00:07:13,339 --> 00:07:16,840
(Relationship status report)

76
00:07:50,410 --> 00:07:53,520
I thought I would never see you again.

77
00:08:04,459 --> 00:08:05,339
Are you all right?

78
00:08:05,656 --> 00:08:07,266
Dad, are you hurt?

79
00:08:07,938 --> 00:08:08,818
Are you all right?

80
00:08:11,067 --> 00:08:11,947
That's great.

81
00:08:18,393 --> 00:08:19,800
Thank you for saving me.

82
00:08:23,675 --> 00:08:25,087
You're welcome, my old friend.

83
00:08:25,723 --> 00:08:27,381
You need to thank your daughter.

84
00:08:27,422 --> 00:08:28,920
She has found a good son.

85
00:08:30,965 --> 00:08:31,840
Mahadi.

86
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:33,560
What did he say?

87
00:08:34,601 --> 00:08:35,481
Nothing.

88
00:08:37,510 --> 00:08:38,920
Liang, good!

89
00:08:44,745 --> 00:08:46,040
I didn't say anything.

90
00:08:52,546 --> 00:08:53,840
Thank you, old comrade.

91
00:08:53,881 --> 00:08:56,151
I'll celebrate your return
when you're back.

92
00:08:56,384 --> 00:08:57,344
That's the deal.

93
00:08:58,075 --> 00:08:58,955
Okay, goodbye.

94
00:09:01,089 --> 00:09:02,160
Are they back?

95
00:09:02,201 --> 00:09:03,044
Yes.

96
00:09:03,085 --> 00:09:04,200
They arrived at noon.

97
00:09:04,241 --> 00:09:06,175
Now, she's taking her father
to the hospital for a checkup.

98
00:09:07,585 --> 00:09:09,480
You two sure do keep in touch.

99
00:09:10,981 --> 00:09:11,861
Brigade Commander,

100
00:09:16,496 --> 00:09:17,576
this is my relationship report.

101
00:09:20,895 --> 00:09:22,280
-Have you come around?
-Yes.

102
00:09:23,368 --> 00:09:26,920
Redeployment is a problem
but it's hard to meet the right person.

103
00:09:27,271 --> 00:09:28,200
I don't want to miss her.

104
00:09:29,472 --> 00:09:32,381
But Xia Chu's father is
the major problem now,

105
00:09:33,111 --> 00:09:34,431
not your redeployment.

106
00:09:34,631 --> 00:09:37,040
Isaia police have found out that
her father was being framed.

107
00:09:39,039 --> 00:09:41,961
But the matter of him leaking information
has yet to be determined.

108
00:09:42,178 --> 00:09:43,058
Leaking information?

109
00:09:43,631 --> 00:09:47,440
He used his personal mailbox
to discuss work with his assistant,

110
00:09:47,991 --> 00:09:49,280
causing the leakage of information.

111
00:09:49,895 --> 00:09:52,335
Now the Institute of Chemistry
has initiated the investigation.

112
00:09:52,951 --> 00:09:54,591
There was no final outcome...

113
00:09:55,311 --> 00:09:56,991
before he went to Isaia.

114
00:10:02,973 --> 00:10:03,873
What are you trying to say?

115
00:10:10,975 --> 00:10:11,855
Okay.

116
00:10:12,788 --> 00:10:13,668
Okay.

117
00:10:13,985 --> 00:10:15,865
Stop pretending with me.

118
00:10:16,473 --> 00:10:18,793
I know you must be
feeling bad now.

119
00:10:19,958 --> 00:10:22,008
I was your age once.

120
00:10:22,117 --> 00:10:25,240
I can see you're currently
very confused about this.

121
00:10:25,655 --> 00:10:26,775
You're mostly thinking...

122
00:10:28,038 --> 00:10:29,078
that you, as a soldier,

123
00:10:29,937 --> 00:10:31,497
can't protect the one you love,

124
00:10:31,951 --> 00:10:33,661
can't give her a decent family,

125
00:10:35,656 --> 00:10:37,656
can't show up when
she needs you the most.

126
00:10:37,871 --> 00:10:39,879
You must be very torn,

127
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:40,840
and very wrong.

128
00:10:41,856 --> 00:10:42,726
Report!

129
00:10:42,871 --> 00:10:44,600
Haven't you had
this kind of feeling before?

130
00:10:45,432 --> 00:10:46,432
Liang Mu Ze,

131
00:10:48,071 --> 00:10:49,181
the words that I'm about to say,

132
00:10:50,143 --> 00:10:51,854
I'm saying them as a brother...

133
00:10:52,671 --> 00:10:56,631
and an old soldier instead of
as a Brigade Commander.

134
00:10:58,184 --> 00:10:59,064
Let me tell you,

135
00:11:00,122 --> 00:11:01,042
you and I...

136
00:11:02,031 --> 00:11:03,400
are professional soldiers.

137
00:11:04,047 --> 00:11:06,047
Since we choose to put this uniform on,

138
00:11:06,694 --> 00:11:09,520
we have to shoulder
the responsibility as soldiers.

139
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:14,880
Everything is non-negotiable
in front of the national interest.

140
00:11:16,084 --> 00:11:18,582
What is professional to a soldier?

141
00:11:19,352 --> 00:11:20,480
This is professional.

142
00:11:21,924 --> 00:11:22,804
I understand.

143
00:11:22,967 --> 00:11:23,960
If there's nothing else,

144
00:11:24,711 --> 00:11:25,591
I'll head back first.

145
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:29,790
Come back here.

146
00:11:31,375 --> 00:11:32,455
You're being surly.

147
00:11:33,231 --> 00:11:35,692
I know
you still have a knot in your heart.

148
00:11:36,136 --> 00:11:37,016
How about this?

149
00:11:38,183 --> 00:11:39,440
I'll allow you to take a half day off.

150
00:11:39,671 --> 00:11:40,671
Just go to the hospital.

151
00:11:41,119 --> 00:11:42,040
And...

152
00:11:42,081 --> 00:11:44,385
submit your relationship status report
to the Special Branch for approval.

153
00:11:44,982 --> 00:11:46,302
Adjust your form and...

154
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:48,711
report to me!

155
00:11:48,752 --> 00:11:49,640
Thank you, Brigade Commander!

156
00:11:54,071 --> 00:11:54,960
This brat!

157
00:12:00,351 --> 00:12:01,600
Stay for a few more days.

158
00:12:02,007 --> 00:12:04,667
At least wait until we obtain
the result of the medical checkup.

159
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:07,360
You're lying.
You didn't want me to stay here.

160
00:12:07,871 --> 00:12:09,271
How am I lying?

161
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:11,201
I have to hurry back.

162
00:12:11,242 --> 00:12:14,280
Your mother must've missed me
since I've left home for days.

163
00:12:14,839 --> 00:12:16,759
I already called Ms. Lan.

164
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:19,181
She said just take your time.

165
00:12:21,655 --> 00:12:23,175
Girl, I can't stay.

166
00:12:24,207 --> 00:12:25,487
I miss your mother too.

167
00:12:27,861 --> 00:12:28,741
Someone fainted!

168
00:12:32,381 --> 00:12:33,316
Step aside! Step aside!

169
00:12:33,357 --> 00:12:34,597
Don't touch her!

170
00:12:36,923 --> 00:12:38,123
Go get the transfer bed.

171
00:13:15,741 --> 00:13:16,621
Uncle Xia,

172
00:13:18,349 --> 00:13:19,720
have you finished the medical checkup?

173
00:13:23,216 --> 00:13:24,096
Yes, I have.

174
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:25,559
I'm here for Xia Chu.

175
00:13:26,989 --> 00:13:27,949
She...

176
00:13:28,421 --> 00:13:29,501
is rescuing the patient.

177
00:13:35,822 --> 00:13:37,772
I've called a cab.

178
00:13:38,391 --> 00:13:39,271
It'll be here soon.

179
00:13:39,697 --> 00:13:40,577
I'm leaving.

180
00:13:40,950 --> 00:13:41,830
Where are you going?

181
00:13:43,094 --> 00:13:43,974
To home.

182
00:13:44,727 --> 00:13:45,607
I'm going back to Dong'an.

183
00:13:48,391 --> 00:13:49,680
Let me send you off.

184
00:13:52,351 --> 00:13:53,231
No need for that.

185
00:14:13,081 --> 00:14:14,201
I heard from them that...

186
00:14:14,688 --> 00:14:17,591
you played a big part in solving
the matter of Isaia.

187
00:14:18,431 --> 00:14:20,400
I was saved, thanks to you.

188
00:14:20,911 --> 00:14:21,791
Thank you.

189
00:14:22,037 --> 00:14:22,917
Uncle Xia,

190
00:14:23,551 --> 00:14:24,431
you're welcome.

191
00:14:24,671 --> 00:14:27,511
But don't you think that
I'll let Xia Chu be with you...

192
00:14:28,431 --> 00:14:30,341
just because you helped me.

193
00:14:31,942 --> 00:14:32,920
Uncle Xia,

194
00:14:32,961 --> 00:14:34,281
case by case,

195
00:14:34,431 --> 00:14:36,911
I'll help you whether you approve or not.

196
00:14:37,220 --> 00:14:38,487
Even if you don't approve,

197
00:14:38,528 --> 00:14:39,408
I'll help you too.

198
00:14:41,016 --> 00:14:43,440
But Xia Chu and I will be together...

199
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,511
no matter what.

200
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:05,720
Xia Chu.

201
00:15:12,904 --> 00:15:13,784
Have you seen my father?

202
00:15:14,022 --> 00:15:15,440
I've seen him, he just left.

203
00:15:16,470 --> 00:15:17,350
Wait for me.

204
00:15:25,071 --> 00:15:25,951
Dad!

205
00:15:29,241 --> 00:15:30,480
Didn't I tell you to wait for me?

206
00:15:32,537 --> 00:15:33,520
Liang Mu Ze is here.

207
00:15:33,871 --> 00:15:34,911
So what?

208
00:15:35,728 --> 00:15:36,768
Are you afraid of meeting him?

209
00:15:39,158 --> 00:15:40,038
A bit.

210
00:15:41,031 --> 00:15:43,194
Perhaps it's the legacy
of the first meeting...

211
00:15:43,234 --> 00:15:45,031
with your grandfather back then.

212
00:15:45,471 --> 00:15:48,231
I flinched when I saw someone
in a military uniform.

213
00:15:49,341 --> 00:15:50,600
I doubt it.

214
00:15:51,039 --> 00:15:52,279
Grandpa is such a kind man.

215
00:15:54,397 --> 00:15:55,917
That's because you're his granddaughter.

216
00:15:56,197 --> 00:15:58,157
He is always rough on me.

217
00:15:58,736 --> 00:16:01,351
He always thinks that
your mother loses out in marrying me.

218
00:16:02,422 --> 00:16:06,711
You still remember how Grandpa opposed
your marriage with Ms. Lan back then?

219
00:16:06,862 --> 00:16:07,742
Of course.

220
00:16:08,311 --> 00:16:09,630
He always wanted to
find your mother someone...

221
00:16:09,671 --> 00:16:10,711
who's a soldier like him.

222
00:16:11,110 --> 00:16:12,677
And he always persuaded
your mother to leave me.

223
00:16:13,671 --> 00:16:14,951
He said that to my face several times.

224
00:16:15,271 --> 00:16:17,480
Can I forget such hurtful words?

225
00:16:18,784 --> 00:16:20,160
So...

226
00:16:20,201 --> 00:16:21,881
Don't be like my grandfather.

227
00:16:22,271 --> 00:16:25,520
Don't be rough on Liang Mu Ze and
persuade him to break up with me.

228
00:16:26,054 --> 00:16:27,791
He'll remember you
for the rest of his life,

229
00:16:27,832 --> 00:16:29,285
if we become man and wife in the future.

230
00:16:29,587 --> 00:16:32,200
Don't you think it'd be awkward?

231
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:38,756
Don't vent your anger on Liang Mu Ze...

232
00:16:38,797 --> 00:16:40,757
just because my grandfather
was hard on you.

233
00:16:41,311 --> 00:16:42,440
I didn't vent my anger.

234
00:16:52,423 --> 00:16:54,183
I just think that
my daughter is too excellent.

235
00:16:55,313 --> 00:16:57,560
No one around you deserves to have you.

236
00:17:02,656 --> 00:17:04,640
Your grandfather might think that
too back then.

237
00:17:06,141 --> 00:17:07,520
But I really like him,

238
00:17:09,023 --> 00:17:10,344
I want to be with him.

239
00:17:15,959 --> 00:17:17,799
The cab is here, I'm leaving.

240
00:17:24,854 --> 00:17:25,734
Girl,

241
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:32,431
no parents in this world
could ever win their kids.

242
00:17:33,566 --> 00:17:34,766
Your grandfather can't,

243
00:17:36,391 --> 00:17:37,351
neither can I.

244
00:17:46,791 --> 00:17:48,631
Dad, I love you!

245
00:17:52,436 --> 00:17:53,680
She is my daughter.

246
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:55,671
I can see that.

247
00:17:56,111 --> 00:17:57,471
She's like you.

248
00:18:03,896 --> 00:18:06,200
She is a doctor from Hospital 109.

249
00:18:07,361 --> 00:18:08,352
She is a heart surgeon.

250
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,800
She is glowing...

251
00:18:14,204 --> 00:18:15,814
like an angel...

252
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,640
when she's rescuing the patients.

253
00:18:31,094 --> 00:18:32,534
My daughter...

254
00:18:38,517 --> 00:18:39,640
has grown up.

255
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:51,160
I handed in the relationship report.

256
00:18:55,542 --> 00:18:58,360
But Dong said it can't be
approved at the moment.

257
00:19:01,048 --> 00:19:02,360
Is it because of my father?

258
00:19:03,456 --> 00:19:04,336
Yes.

259
00:19:05,136 --> 00:19:07,416
The decision can only be made
after the result of...

260
00:19:08,381 --> 00:19:09,381
the investigation is obtained.

261
00:19:22,303 --> 00:19:23,640
I thought it was a big deal.

262
00:19:23,681 --> 00:19:25,241
We just have to wait.

263
00:19:25,968 --> 00:19:27,951
We'll get the result no matter
how long it takes.

264
00:19:28,304 --> 00:19:31,000
And I believe that
my father will be fine.

265
00:19:33,431 --> 00:19:34,880
But I don't wish to wait any longer.

266
00:19:34,921 --> 00:19:36,360
I'm soon to be redeployed.

267
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:40,111
I want to tell everyone
that Xia Chu is my girlfriend.

268
00:19:46,488 --> 00:19:47,888
Don't be afraid, Braised Egg.

269
00:19:48,298 --> 00:19:51,295
We pulled through when we were
in such a difficult situation in Isaia.

270
00:19:51,336 --> 00:19:53,320
Now, we just have to wait a little bit.

271
00:19:55,329 --> 00:19:56,400
And I have a feeling that...

272
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,711
we'll have a happy life in the future.

273
00:20:00,168 --> 00:20:01,280
You need to have faith.

274
